reviewText: The classes are very shalow. I would have like more readings or material so that we could go deeper into the subject.

It is an interesting course, focussed on tools to handle change as a person and build resilience.The course deals with a lot of tools and provides exercises, but I find the level of the topics too shallow. For example, the section on habits is just a few minutes, and explains the bare minimum. That is not enough to really understand how it works and be able to apply it. And this applies to most of the topics.Also, the explanation video's where very short and at times difficult to understand for a non native English speaker. Several times I had to read the text to understand what was said. Adding more slides with text and pictures would really help. And talk slower.What can help to improve the course is to add materials (reading, video's, podcasts) from other sources for a deeper dive in the topics.

Es bueno el curso, sin embargo el material de apoyo es muy básico y entiendo que es mas practico, sin embargo seria bueno agregar mas información teórica. Con el cual podamos consultar en otro momento y poder tener mas claros los temas.
This course has helped me to look at change in a different way. I have amazed with kind of tools available for helping transformation as leader at work and in personal life.

This is a good course because it will confront you with things that you need to work on. However, as with all online courses, it does require a certain discipline. The agile workbook is great, but you do have to actually do it to gain insights. Overall, I think I learned the things I needed to learn more, so this is a great kickstart, but you have to now also continously practice and actually do the things that were taught in this class.
Great course to help reframe and centre yourself

Solid but basic course for leading yourself through change. Consists of practical technics.  Strength - instructor with good presentation skills, expiations contain link to neuroscience. Basic but ready-to-use workbook opportunities to improve - quizzes are very basic, there is no feedback or opportunity to ask instructor a questions. Recommend as introduction before deep diving into theme of change.

Oxana is truly a great orator. The way she has designed this course makes you believe that you can achieve all your goals easily and motivates me to better myself. This course has helped me to understand things in a broader perspective.

Practical advice and tips for managing change in your life. Very internal focused, can be applied to any situation of change, not just work. Clearly presented, easy to follow. I do wish the course had more of an agile methodology tone though rather than being a resilient person in general. Would like more content on leading teams which practice agile development methodology and getting organizations started and used to the principles of agile development methodology.
Focuses on really important things. Short fragmented videos are a bit annoying still. Feels like i spent more time sometimes just switching between them rather than learning.
